pageContext.claim: “But we need Democrat votes to get the border fully secured, fully taken care of. We're getting close. Mexico has been fantastic. We had a meeting with Mexico. For 45 years, people have been trying to get Mexico [to stop migration from Central America], and they weren't able to get it. And we got it in one day -- everything.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump has a tendency to claim his deals have eluded politicians for 45 (or 50) years, and that appears to be the case here. There is no basis to make this claim.
